thread.title: Washington State Cougars to Oregon Ducks: 'You have died of dysentery'
thread.title_full: Washington State Cougars to Oregon Ducks: 'You have died of dysentery' | OregonLive.com

author: Tyson Alger | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Washington State Cougars to Oregon Ducks: 'You have died of dysentery'
text:
EUGENE -- Oregon has beaten up on the Pac-12 for much of the last decade.
It doesn't appear that its opponents have forgotten.
After Washington State's upset 45-38 double-overtime win over the Ducks, someone over in the Cougars' communications department decided to twist the knife just a little extra.
Oregon, wearing Lewis & Clark-inspired "Pioneer" uniforms, may have set itself up for this one:
#GoCougs pic.twitter.com/X4txXBLoqd
— WSU Cougars (@WSUCougars) October 11, 2015
And it's not the first time the Ducks have been trolled after a loss. When Arizona beat Oregon a year ago, this post came across the UA Twitter feed, taking a jab at Oregon's "Win the Day" slogan.
#WonTheDay (again) pic.twitter.com/dCxcmZjhfa
— Arizona Athletics (@AZATHLETICS) October 3, 2014
